{"LanguageCode":"en","Chapter":56,"Index":"056","Name":"Al-Waqia","TranslatedName":"The Inevitable","ArabicName":"سُوْرَةُ الْوَاقِعَةِ","Revelation":"Mecca","RevelationOrder":46,"VerseCount":96,"SajdaCount":0,"JuzStart":27,"JuzEnd":27,"VerseStart":4980,"VerseEnd":5075,"ManzilStart":7,"ManzilEnd":7,"RukuStart":469,"RukuEnd":471,"MaqraStart":214,"MaqraEnd":215,"PageStart":534,"PageEnd":537,"Summaries":["<p>This is a Makki Surah revealed in the early Makkan period. This is the seventh Surah of the group of Surahs that began with Surah Qaf (no. 50). It completes the subject of death, resurrection and divine judgment. The Surah has 96 verses in 3 sections.</p>","<p>The Surah talks about the resurrection that will definitely take place. It is a fact undeniable. The human beings then will be in three different groups. The faithful are of two types: those who are the pioneers and are foremost in their faith and struggle in the path of Allah. They are a large number from amongst the earlier community and a small from among the later generations. Then the rest of the people are believers and those who oppose the faith. Allah's rewards are for the faithful and his anger and chastisement is waiting for the opponents of faith.</p>","<p>The Surah then invites human beings to think about themselves and the things that they use daily and consider who created all these things. It talks about the Qur’an and its profound and consistent message and then finally reminds about death and the coming end of every being.</p>","<ol>","\t<li>The reality will come to pass. The humanity will be in three camps: people of the right hand, people of the left hand and the foremost in faith. The reward of the believers.</li>","\t<li>The guilty and their punishment. Arguments about the Tawhid and Akhirah.</li>","\t<li>The Qur’an and its consistent message. Reminder about death, divine judgment and the reward and punishment.</li>","</ol>"],"Verses":[{"Verse":1,"Text":"إِذَا وَقَعَتِ ٱلۡوَاقِعَةُ","End":"١"},{"Verse":2,"Text":"لَيۡسَ لِوَقۡعَتِهَا كَاذِبَةٌ","End":"٢"},{"Verse":3,"Text":"خَافِضَةٞ رَّافِعَةٌ","End":"٣"},{"Verse":4,"Text":"إِذَا رُجَّتِ ٱلۡأَرۡضُ رَجّٗا","End":"٤"},{"Verse":5,"Text":"وَبُسَّتِ ٱلۡجِبَالُ بَسّٗا","End":"٥"},{"Verse":6,"Text":"فَكَانَتۡ هَبَآءٗ مُّنۢبَثّٗا","End":"٦"},{"Verse":7,"Text":"وَكُنتُمۡ أَزۡوَٰجٗا ثَلَٰثَةٗ","End":"٧"},{"Verse":8,"Text":"فَأَصۡحَٰبُ ٱلۡمَيۡمَنَةِ مَآ أَصۡحَٰبُ ٱلۡمَيۡمَنَةِ","End":"٨"},{"Verse":9,"Text":"وَأَصۡحَٰبُ ٱلۡمَشۡـَٔمَةِ مَآ أَصۡحَٰبُ ٱلۡمَشۡـَٔمَةِ","End":"٩"},{"Verse":10,"Text":"وَٱلسَّـٰبِقُونَ ٱلسَّـٰبِقُونَ","End":"١٠"},{"Verse":11,"Text":"أُوْلَـٰٓئِكَ ٱلۡمُقَرَّبُونَ","End":"١١"},{"Verse":12,"Text":"فِي جَنَّـٰتِ ٱلنَّعِيمِ","End":"١٢"},{"Verse":13,"Text":"ثُلَّةٞ مِّنَ ٱلۡأَوَّلِينَ","End":"١٣"},{"Verse":14,"Text":"وَقَلِيلٞ مِّنَ ٱلۡأٓخِرِينَ","End":"١٤"},{"Verse":15,"Text":"عَلَىٰ سُرُرٖ مَّوۡضُونَةٖ","End":"١٥"},{"Verse":16,"Text":"مُّتَّكِـِٔينَ عَلَيۡهَا مُتَقَٰبِلِينَ","End":"١٦"},{"Verse":17,"Text":"يَطُوفُ عَلَيۡهِمۡ وِلۡدَٰنٞ مُّخَلَّدُونَ","End":"١٧"},{"Verse":18,"Text":"بِأَكۡوَابٖ وَأَبَارِيقَ وَكَأۡسٖ مِّن مَّعِينٖ","End":"١٨"},{"Verse":19,"Text":"لَّا يُصَدَّعُونَ عَنۡهَا وَلَا يُنزِفُونَ","End":"١٩"},{"Verse":20,"Text":"وَفَٰكِهَةٖ مِّمَّا يَتَخَيَّرُونَ","End":"٢٠"},{"Verse":21,"Text":"وَلَحۡمِ طَيۡرٖ مِّمَّا يَشۡتَهُونَ","End":"٢١"},{"Verse":22,"Text":"وَحُورٌ عِينٞ","End":"٢٢"},{"Verse":23,"Text":"كَأَمۡثَٰلِ ٱللُّؤۡلُوِٕ ٱلۡمَكۡنُونِ","End":"٢٣"},{"Verse":24,"Text":"جَزَآءَۢ بِمَا كَانُواْ يَعۡمَلُونَ","End":"٢٤"},{"Verse":25,"Text":"لَا يَسۡمَعُونَ فِيهَا لَغۡوٗا وَلَا تَأۡثِيمًا","End":"٢٥"},{"Verse":26,"Text":"إِلَّا قِيلٗا سَلَٰمٗا سَلَٰمٗا","End":"٢٦"},{"Verse":27,"Text":"وَأَصۡحَٰبُ ٱلۡيَمِينِ مَآ أَصۡحَٰبُ ٱلۡيَمِينِ","End":"٢٧"},{"Verse":28,"Text":"فِي سِدۡرٖ مَّخۡضُودٖ","End":"٢٨"},{"Verse":29,"Text":"وَطَلۡحٖ مَّنضُودٖ","End":"٢٩"},{"Verse":30,"Text":"وَظِلّٖ مَّمۡدُودٖ","End":"٣٠"},{"Verse":31,"Text":"وَمَآءٖ مَّسۡكُوبٖ","End":"٣١"},{"Verse":32,"Text":"و